The given expression is equal to
\(\begin{aligned}
& \log _{n} 2+\log _{n} 3+\ldots+\log _{n} 53 \\
=& \log _{n}(2.3 \ldots 53)=\log _{n} 53 !=\frac{1}{\log _{53 !} n}
\end{aligned}\)

We have, \(\sqrt{\left(-x^{2}+4 x-3\right)}>6-2 x\)
This inequation is equivalent to the collection of two systems, of inequations
\(\begin{array}{l}
\text { i.e. }\left\{\begin{array} { c } 
{ 6 - 2 x \geq 0 } \\
{ - x ^ { 2 } + 4 x - 3 > ( 6 - 2 x ) ^ { 2 } }
\end{array} \text { and } \left\{\begin{array}{c}
6-2 x < 0 \\
-x^{2}+4 x-3 \geq 0
\end{array}\right.\right. \\
\Rightarrow\left\{\begin{array} { c } 
{ x \leq 3 } \\
{ ( x - 3 ) ( 5 x - 1 3 ) < 0 }
\end{array} \text { and } \left\{\begin{array}{c}
x>3 \\
(x-1)(x-3) \leq 0
\end{array}\right.\right. \\
\Rightarrow\left\{\begin{array} { c } 
{ x > 3 } \\
{ \frac { 1 3 } { 5 } < x < 3 }
\end{array} \text { and } \left\{\begin{array}{l}
x > 3 \\
1 \leq x < 3
\end{array}\right.\right.
\end{array}\)
The second system has no solution and the first system has solution in the interval \(\left(\frac{13}{5} < x < 3\right\}\)
Hence, \(x \in\left(\frac{13}{5}, 3\right)\) is the set of solution of the original inequation.
